                            <comment id="12520858" author="jimk" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2007 16:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Log output from test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12520865" author="stack" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2007 16:22:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like hadoop-1730 to me.  Waiting on tests before committing it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12520879" author="stack" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2007 18:22:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If one of the two daughter splits had been removed and then the META scanner ran, a get on the info on the removed region would come back empty generating the IllegalArgumentException causing the scanner to exit.  Because the meta scanner wasn&apos;t running, parents were not being cleaned up and so the test was failling.  Usually when tests ran, both daughters had been cleaned by the time the META scanner ran and all just worked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closing because &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-254&quot; title=&quot;[hbase] unexpected null value causes META scanner to exit (silently)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-254&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-1730&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, just committed, should fix this issue (Can reopen if happens again).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
